<p>Relevant. Relevant goals are, well, relevant. â€œLearn to play some guitar chords to play while sitting at the campfireâ€ is a shitty goal, because what if you donâ€™t like camping? What if you canâ€™t stand the sound of an acoustic guitar? What if you donâ€™t want to spend hundreds of dollars on a guitar? If these questions are making you reconsider, itâ€™s possible that this isnâ€™t a very relevant goal to you. Instead, perhaps youâ€™re really into woodwind instruments, and perhaps you only want to invest a few dollars. Maybe you should learn the recorder instead.</p>

